manifest_analysis.title:
Application Data can be Backed up
[android:allowBackup=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: This flag allows anyone to backup your application data via adb. It allows users who have enabled USB debugging to copy application data off of the device.
manifest_analysis.name: Application Data can be Backed up [android:allowBackup=true]

manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (app.codecellar.embitwallet.MainActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

manifest_analysis.title:
Activity (app.codecellar.embitwallet.MainActivity) is not Protected.
An intent-filter exists.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. The presence of intent-filter indicates that the Activity is explicitly exported.
manifest_analysis.name: is not Protected.An intent-filter exists.

playstore_details.title: Embit Wallet - Bitcoin testnet wallet and messages
playstore_details.description:
Embit Wallet is a de-centralized peer-to-peer bitcoin wallet that stores open and closed keys on local device and interacts with blockchain to allows users to send and receive bitcoin easily with embedded message, browse transactions history and current balance for each address.

Main features:
Interaction also with the testnet blockchain.
Full bech32 and SegWit support.
Mock function of the transaction.
Scanner for addresses and private keys.
Dynamic fee estimation and custom fee settings.
Backup and renew wallet keys.
Import private key from paper wallet or brainwallet.
Sign and verify message like Bitcoin-Qt.
URI scheme that allow for linking to the app.
Account book and sender address book.
System notification for received and sent coins.
Bitcoin ticker and market graph.
One of a kind:
Send secure messages with bitcoin protocol
(end-to-end encryption or plain text)
playstore_details.summary: The first mobile wallet to send secure messages with bitcoin protocol
playstore_details.summaryHTML: The first mobile wallet to send secure messages with bitcoin protocol
